<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=35&amp;p=263#p263"><![CDATA[
Not to sway you away from the cool factor ( I hate  when people do that) but you can acheive similar results with a dance dance revo stype ps2 pad, a ps2 comtroller to USB adaptor and a joystick to midi program on a pc. Something to keep in mind if you cant find a  power pad (playing on one will relly tear it apart) or are technophobically inclined..<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59">herr_prof</a> — Tue Nov 23, 2004 10:16 pm</p><hr />
